- "Total access time" is the sum of all access durations for a dataset;
- "Shine the brightest in the night sky" is a metaphor for being the most accessed or popular.

- 'crown jewel' refers to the most valuable or prominent item in a collection;
- 'unique visitors' refers to the number of distinct users;
- 'access time' refers to the total duration of access in seconds.

- 'numerical' data type refers to datasets containing numerical values;
- 'download' access type indicates that users have downloaded the dataset;
- 'unique users' refers to distinct user IDs.

- 'numerical datasets' refer to datasets containing numerical data;
- 'over a thousand gems' refers to datasets with more than 1000 data points;
- 'most recently updated' means the datasets with the highest version numbers;
- 'most widely accessed' refers to datasets accessed by the largest number of unique users.

